<taxonomicName id="14C75FFD228C5EA13F9A0B112389846F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene cucubalus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cucubalus">
<emphasis id="8C356E88CF0BB5988410BC0881301A1A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Silene cucubalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wib. (= 
<taxonomicName id="6DEE28EC20DE1E258CB1935F1F1A54B5" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene vulgaris" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis id="EA8C7FFA1D175E45D4CBC9B1FF14E3D0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Silene vulgaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Moench) Garcke) and 
<bibRefCitation id="2561F6A94A681C56F985EFB19C8CB137" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4109291" author="Marsden-Jones, EM" journalOrPublisher="Bothalia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B33" refString="Marsden-Jones, EM, Turrill, WB, 1957. The bladder campions: Silenemaritima and S.vulgaris. The Ray Society, London, 1-378. https://doi.org/10.2307/4109291" title="The bladder campions: Silenemaritima and S. vulgaris. The Ray Society, London, 1 - 378." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4109291" year="1957">Marsden-Jones and Turrill (1957)</bibRefCitation>
recognized the name as a part of the 
<taxonomicName id="F642DD84828EBD22EFD2C11EE69CD035" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene vulgaris" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vulgaris">
<emphasis id="1EBE7D7F095A09A70C86FB8D93196884" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Silene vulgaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-assemblage but used the name in a highly informal way. The name is not mentioned in 
<bibRefCitation id="023BA7E341E5E19440B029A3AB15E50B" author="Chater, AO" editor="Tutin, TG" journalOrPublisher="2. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="191 - 218" refId="B11" refString="Chater, AO, Walters, SM, Akeroyd, JR, 1993. Silene L. In: Tutin, TG, Burges, NA, Chater, AO, Edmonson, JR, Heywood, VH, Moore, DM, Valentine, DH, Walters, SM, Webb, DA, Eds., Flora Europaea, ed. 2. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge: 191 - 218" title="Silene L." volumeTitle="Flora Europaea, ed." year="1993">Chater et al. (1993)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="6290E22E373B9BF2BD7A2CF45FA1CB93" author="Aeschimann, D" journalOrPublisher="Candollea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="57 - 98" refId="B1" refString="Aeschimann, D, 1985. Etude biosystematique du Silene vulgaris s.l. (Caryophyllaceae) dans le domaine alpin. Candollea 40: 57 - 98" title="Etude biosystematique du Silene vulgaris s. l. (Caryophyllaceae) dans le domaine alpin." volume="40" year="1985">Aeschimann (1985)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="4BD7D884C0D35D1CB49C4DFCDC016DD4" author="Pignatti, S" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B46" refString="Pignatti, S, 1982. Flora d'Italia, Vol. 1. Edagricole, Bologna, 1-790." title="Flora d'Italia, Vol. 1. Edagricole, Bologna, 1 - 790." year="1982">Pignatti (1982)</bibRefCitation>
or 
<bibRefCitation id="7706BE1EC54B95A75FEEF93A59733635" author="Greuter, W" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B23" refString="Greuter, W, Burdet, HM, Long, G, 1984. Med-Checklist, 1. Geneve and Berlin." title="Med-Checklist, 1. Geneve and Berlin." year="1984">Greuter et al. (1984)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="5D9E1991609FE7D5C87114BD7725D3B8" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene linearis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis id="8F1BDCA9808BEE49C1148413476148DC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Silene linearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Decne. has been suggested to be conserved against 
<taxonomicName id="F76AE13041929A061A6E71CABD4BADB6" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene linearis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearis">
<emphasis id="4D18DAB01E28BB067459664697D49C8B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Silene linearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Sweet (Eggens &amp; al., in press).
